  <title translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For MODFLOW and PHAST models, </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns then number of the uppermost layer for which </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="ActiveOnLayer" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">ActiveOnLayer</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns True. If no layer is active, </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns 0. </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can only be used when it is being evaluated at cells (MODFLOW) or elements (PHAST). It can not be used when it is being evaluated at nodes in PHAST. </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HighestActiveLayers</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> should not be used with SUTRA models. </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">HighestActiveLayer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> should not be used to set the Z formula of a specified head boundary.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
